 and finished narration audio, with the ability to leave and come back later without losing progress.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:21:1. Genre selection from a curated genre list.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:22:2. Tone selection from options preconfigured for the chosen genre.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:26:6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet generation and editing.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:48:- User chat can propose structured actions such as selecting a tone or refining beats.\\ndocs/product-brief.md:80:- create and revise a bedtime story plan\\nprompts/43-brief-normalization-service.md:10:- Build a backend service that extracts likely protagonist type, setting, emotional goal, constraint notes, bedtime-safety concerns, and candidate motifs from the user\\u2019s brief.\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:87:    __tablename__ = \\\"genres\\\"\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:92:    bedtime_safety_notes: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(Text)\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:97:    tone_profiles: Mapped[list[\\\"ToneProfile\\\"]] = relationship(\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:98:        back_populates=\\\"genre\\\",\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:101:    sessions: Mapped[list[\\\"StorySession\\\"]] = relationship(back_populates=\\\"selected_genre\\\")\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:104:        Index(\\\"ix_genres_sort_order\\\", \\\"sort_order\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:105:        Index(\\\"ix_genres_is_active\\\", \\\"is_active\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:110:    __tablename__ = \\\"tone_profiles\\\"\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:112:    genre_id: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:114:        ForeignKey(\\\"genres.id\\\", ondelete=\\\"CASCADE\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:120:    bedtime_notes: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(Text)\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:125:    genre: Mapped[\\\"Genre\\\"] = relationship(back_populates=\\\"tone_profiles\\\")\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:126:    sessions: Mapped[list[\\\"StorySession\\\"]] = relationship(back_populates=\\\"selected_tone_profile\\\")\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:129:        UniqueConstraint(\\\"genre_id\\\", \\\"slug\\\", name=\\\"uq_tone_profiles_genre_id_slug\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:130:        Index(\\\"ix_tone_profiles_genre_id_sort_order\\\", \\\"genre_id\\\", \\\"sort_order\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:131:        Index(\\\"ix_tone_profiles_genre_id_is_active\\\", \\\"genre_id\\\", \\\"is_active\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:155:    selected_genre_id: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:157:        ForeignKey(\\\"genres.id\\\", ondelete=\\\"SET NULL\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:159:    selected_tone_profile_id: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:161:        ForeignKey(\\\"tone_profiles.id\\\", ondelete=\\\"SET NULL\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:165:    selected_genre: Mapped[\\\"Genre | None\\\"] = relationship(back_populates=\\\"sessions\\\")\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:166:    selected_tone_profile: Mapped[\\\"ToneProfile | None\\\"] = relationship(back_populates=\\\"sessions\\\")\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:216:        Index(\\\"ix_story_sessions_selected_genre_id\\\", \\\"selected_genre_id\\\"),\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:332:    bedtime_notes: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(Text)\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:370:    bedtime_notes: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(Text)\\nbackend/app/db/models.py:403:    bedtime_notes: Mapped[str | None] = mapped_column(Text)\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:3:You are building a production-minded local-first application that helps a user create a bedtime story from idea to finished text and finished narration audio.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:25:   - Save-the-Cat beat sheet\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:35:The app is for **bedtime stories**, not generic fiction generation. That means:\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:40:- Tension is allowed, but it should be modulated for bedtime use.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:43:- The narration and UI tone should remain calm, readable, and trustworthy.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:45:Use the research docs in this prompt pack as direct product input, especially the Save The Cat notes and the curated genre/tone catalog.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:52:   - The user selects from the curated genre list.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:54:   - The user is shown preconfigured tone options for the chosen genre.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:64:   - Gemini generates a Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the selected plan.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:143:- Selected genre\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:144:- Selected tone\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:174:- select a tone\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:185:- \\u201cSelected genre: Quest Fantasy\\u201d\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:192:## Save The Cat Expectations\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:194:Use the Save The Cat method as the backbone of planning.\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:204:- a curated genre list\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:205:- per-genre tone options\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:206:- bedtime-suitable arc notes\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:207:- tone descriptors that can guide UI copy and AI prompting\\nprompts/base_prompt.md:209:Do **not** label tones with living or copyrighted-author names. Use generic tone labels and descriptors.\\nprompts/86-completed-session-summary-and-search.md:10:- Enhance the home screen with searching, filtering, or grouping for sessions by status, genre, date, or title.\\ndocs/domain-model.md:26:| `selected_genre_id` | Accepted genre catalog row for the session. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:27:| `selected_tone_profile_id` | Accepted tone profile row for the session. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:49:| `story_session` | Root aggregate for one bedtime-story project. | IDs, title, stage pointers, overall status, timestamps. | Owns the current accepted choices and job pointers. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:51:| `genre` | Curated genre catalog entry. | slug, label, description, bedtime-safety notes. | Backend-owned reference data. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:52:| `tone_profile` | Curated tone option linked to a genre. | `genre_id`, slug, label, descriptors, bedtime notes. | Tone choices are filtered by genre. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:54:| `pitch` | One candidate story premise. | batch or generation group, summary, hook, bedtime notes, selection flag. | `selected_pitch_id` on the session represents the accepted pitch; selection does not require a separate table. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:56:| `beat_sheet` | Structured Save-the-Cat plan. | ordered beats, bedtime-adaptation notes, revision. | Must be editable and versioned. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:70:| 1 | `genre` | Genre | The user accepts a genre for the session. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:71:| 2 | `tone` | Tone | The user accepts a tone profile for the selected genre. |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\\ndocs/domain-model.md:163:   - Example: `genre`, `tone`, and `brief` are `completed`; `pitches` is `in_progress`.\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:9:{\\\"color\\\": \\\"cyan\\\", \\\"emoji\\\": \\\"\\\\ud83d\\\\udee0\\\\ufe0f\\\", \\\"event_type\\\": \\\"Command Finished\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'pwd && rg --files .'\\\", \\\"raw_event\\\": {\\\"item\\\": {\\\"aggregated_output\\\": \\\"/Users/kevin/code/storyteller\\\\n./secrets.example.yaml\\\\n./prompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md\\\\n./prompts/99-release-checklist-and-future-roadmap.md\\\\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/44-pitch-generation-pipeline.md\\\\n./prompts/10-domain-model-and-state-machine.codex.jsonlines\\\\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.md\\\\n./prompts/